we use if else if --> when we need to test multiple conditions

String browser="safari";

if (browser.equals("chrome")) {
	code a;
}else if(browser.("firefox")) {
	code b;
}else if (browser.equals("safari")){
	code c;
}else {
	code d;
}


we use nested if --> when we have 1 condition depend on another condition

if (true){

	code a;

	if (true){
		code b;
	}
}

if{} , else if{}, else{}

-------------------------------
if (false){
	code a;

}else {
	code b;

	if(true){
		code c;
	}
}

